WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

1
00:00:01.668 --> 00:00:04.670
♪

2
00:00:13.013 --> 00:00:14.446
[narrator]
<i>Meet Michael.</i>

3
00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:17.083
<i>This ambitious 22-year-old
has dreams</i>

4
00:00:17.118 --> 00:00:18.985
<i>of traveling through Europe
on foot,</i>

5
00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:21.253
<i>discovering
underserved communities,</i>

6
00:00:21.288 --> 00:00:22.921
<i>and creating
an app that, like,</i>

7
00:00:22.956 --> 00:00:24.956
<i>totally changes the world.</i>

8
00:00:24.991 --> 00:00:27.426
<i>No? That's not you?
You're not Michael?</i>

9
00:00:27.461 --> 00:00:29.328
<i>Sorry. My bad.
Um, let's see.</i>

10
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.296
<i>One second.
I'll have to fire my assistant.</i>

11
00:00:31.331 --> 00:00:32.631
<i>Ah, yes, of course.</i>

12
00:00:32.666 --> 00:00:34.000
<i>Your name would be Jonathan?</i>

13
00:00:34.035 --> 00:00:35.635
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

14
00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:38.771
<i>He wants to get his
personal highest score on...</i>

15
00:00:38.806 --> 00:00:40.506
<i>...Flappy Bird?</i>
[whip crack sound]

16
00:00:40.541 --> 00:00:42.475
<i>Oh, dear God.</i>

17
00:00:42.510 --> 00:00:44.176
<i>Jonathan, meet Kristin.</i>

18
00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:46.780
<i>She is a winner.
Kristin, Jonathan.</i>

19
00:00:46.815 --> 00:00:49.315
<i>He is a... Jonathan.</i>

20
00:00:49.350 --> 00:00:51.550
<i>Now, both of you should be
paying attention</i>

21
00:00:51.585 --> 00:00:53.051
<i>to your Econ teacher.</i>

22
00:00:53.086 --> 00:00:55.555
<i>But since you're not,
I am here to help.</i>

23
00:00:55.590 --> 00:00:57.556
<i>So, forget about class
for the moment.</i>

24
00:00:57.591 --> 00:00:59.325
<i>Forget about
charts and graphs.</i>

25
00:00:59.360 --> 00:01:01.326
<i>Forget about
supply and demand.</i>

26
00:01:01.361 --> 00:01:05.131
<i>Let's talk supply
and dance, man.</i>

27
00:01:05.166 --> 00:01:07.400
<i>Oh, and woman,
of course.</i>

28
00:01:07.435 --> 00:01:09.901
[jazzy music ♪]

29
00:01:11.505 --> 00:01:13.840
<i>Go on, keep walking,</i>

30
00:01:13.875 --> 00:01:15.841
<i>never mind all those
beautiful people</i>

31
00:01:15.876 --> 00:01:17.743
<i>with camera equipment.</i>

32
00:01:17.778 --> 00:01:19.678
<i>Congratulations!</i>

33
00:01:19.713 --> 00:01:22.381
<i>You now both own stores.</i>

34
00:01:22.416 --> 00:01:24.316
<i>Let's see what you can sell.</i>

35
00:01:24.351 --> 00:01:25.618
[cash register dings]

36
00:01:26.586 --> 00:01:28.655
♪

37
00:01:29.623 --> 00:01:30.656
[whooshing]

38
00:01:30.691 --> 00:01:32.191
<i>Might work.</i>

39
00:01:32.226 --> 00:01:34.226
[pop]
<i>Maybe not.</i>

40
00:01:35.463 --> 00:01:37.630
♪

41
00:01:38.498 --> 00:01:39.665
[slap]

42
00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:40.700
[popping]

43
00:01:41.601 --> 00:01:42.768
[cymbal splash]

44
00:01:42.803 --> 00:01:45.136
<i>Oh, well, you tried.</i>

45
00:01:45.171 --> 00:01:47.240
<i>But wait...</i>

46
00:01:47.275 --> 00:01:49.841
♪

47
00:01:49.876 --> 00:01:52.078
<i>There you go, Kristin.</i>

48
00:01:52.113 --> 00:01:54.013
♪

49
00:01:54.048 --> 00:01:55.215
[ding]

50
00:01:57.451 --> 00:01:58.618
[chimes]

51
00:02:00.521 --> 00:02:03.255
♪

52
00:02:05.726 --> 00:02:06.893
[chimes]

53
00:02:09.430 --> 00:02:10.663
<i>Oh, yeah.</i>

54
00:02:12.233 --> 00:02:14.666
♪

55
00:02:22.943 --> 00:02:24.343
<i>Well, it's all right.</i>

56
00:02:24.378 --> 00:02:27.246
<i>If you only had some canes
in your store.</i>

57
00:02:27.281 --> 00:02:28.513
[pop]

58
00:02:28.548 --> 00:02:30.783
<i>But, maybe you do.</i>

59
00:02:30.818 --> 00:02:34.753
<i>And a few extra bucks
for your extra effort.</i>

60
00:02:34.788 --> 00:02:37.190
<i>That's not such a bad deal,
is it?</i>

61
00:02:39.226 --> 00:02:41.060
<i>Double yeah.</i>

62
00:02:41.095 --> 00:02:43.261
♪

63
00:02:43.296 --> 00:02:45.498
<i>But both of you could have
made a few more bucks</i>

64
00:02:45.533 --> 00:02:47.266
<i>if you had more canes.</i>

65
00:02:47.301 --> 00:02:49.635
<i>Are you going to let that
happen again?</i>

66
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.571
<i>My suggestion:
order more.</i>

67
00:02:52.606 --> 00:02:54.273
[muffled talking]

68
00:02:54.308 --> 00:02:56.241
♪

69
00:03:04.518 --> 00:03:06.585
[ding, ding, ding]

70
00:03:07.288 --> 00:03:10.021
♪

71
00:03:15.228 --> 00:03:16.428
[chuckling]
<i>Wait,</i>

72
00:03:16.463 --> 00:03:18.130
<i>with the demand so high,</i>

73
00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:22.001
<i>looks like Kristin can squeeze
out a few more bucks.</i>

74
00:03:22.036 --> 00:03:23.335
[all gasp]

75
00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:25.805
<i>Two can play at that game.</i>

76
00:03:26.773 --> 00:03:27.773
[ding]

77
00:03:29.576 --> 00:03:31.410
♪

78
00:03:35.783 --> 00:03:36.881
[boing]

79
00:03:38.786 --> 00:03:42.021
<i>Wonderful.
People are loving the canes.</i>

80
00:03:42.056 --> 00:03:43.421
<i>Remember earlier,
when I said</i>

81
00:03:43.456 --> 00:03:45.625
<i>to forget about
charts and graphs?</i>

82
00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:47.293
<i>I lied.</i>
[laughs]

83
00:03:47.328 --> 00:03:49.161
<i>Pause!</i>
[record scratching]

84
00:03:49.196 --> 00:03:51.130
<i>Not you guys.</i>

85
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:54.166 line:10%
<i>What you were seeing
is how price</i>

86
00:03:54.201 --> 00:03:56.168 line:10%
<i>is directly related
to the quantity supplied</i>

87
00:03:56.203 --> 00:03:58.036 line:10%
<i>from the shop owner's
point of view.</i>

88
00:03:58.071 --> 00:03:59.838 line:10%
<i>The higher the price,
the more the shop owner's</i>

89
00:03:59.873 --> 00:04:01.506 line:10%
<i>willing to supply
higher quantities,</i>

90
00:04:01.541 --> 00:04:02.708
<i>because it's worth it.</i>

91
00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:04.410 line:10%
<i>People are buying
and making money.</i>

92
00:04:04.445 --> 00:04:05.678
<i>All is good.</i>

93
00:04:05.713 --> 00:04:07.913 line:10%
<i>This is called
the supply curve.</i>

94
00:04:07.948 --> 00:04:09.281
<i>Un-pause!</i>

95
00:04:09.316 --> 00:04:11.083
<i>But you see,
at some point,</i>

96
00:04:11.118 --> 00:04:12.385
<i>if your price gets too high,</i>

97
00:04:12.420 --> 00:04:14.553
<i>your customers may not
be able to afford it.</i>

98
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:16.588
<i>And with your high
quantity of supply,</i>

99
00:04:16.623 --> 00:04:18.925
<i>you may end up
with a surplus.</i>

100
00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:20.660
♪

101
00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.163
<i>Now what are you going to do?</i>

102
00:04:25.198 --> 00:04:27.233
[rain pattering,
thunder rumbling]

103
00:04:27.268 --> 00:04:28.801
<i>Oh, great.</i>

104
00:04:28.836 --> 00:04:30.570
<i>You're just going to give up,</i>

105
00:04:30.605 --> 00:04:34.173
<i>live your life with a store
full of unsold canes.</i>

106
00:04:36.010 --> 00:04:37.076
[buzz]

107
00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:42.348
<i>Lower price, but that's
better than no sale, right?</i>

108
00:04:44.051 --> 00:04:46.385
♪

109
00:04:48.388 --> 00:04:51.856
<i>Oh, this should clear out
some supply for you.</i>

110
00:04:51.891 --> 00:04:54.026
<i>Kristin, what are you doing?</i>

111
00:04:54.061 --> 00:04:56.461
<i>Undercutting your competitor!</i>

112
00:04:56.496 --> 00:04:58.363
<i>I like it!</i>

113
00:04:58.398 --> 00:05:00.533
♪

114
00:05:03.703 --> 00:05:05.705
<i>Here we go again.</i>

115
00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:08.006
♪

116
00:05:15.516 --> 00:05:16.648
<i>There you go.</i>

117
00:05:16.683 --> 00:05:18.751
<i>Canes are flying
off the shelves,</i>

118
00:05:18.786 --> 00:05:21.920
<i>so much so,
you need to order more.</i>

119
00:05:21.955 --> 00:05:23.455
[muffled talking]

120
00:05:25.091 --> 00:05:26.156
<i>Pause!</i>

121
00:05:26.191 --> 00:05:28.326 line:10%
<i>What you were seeing here
is the demand curve</i>

122
00:05:28.361 --> 00:05:30.128 line:10%
<i>and it's from
the customer's point of view.</i>

123
00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:32.065 line:10%
<i>The higher the price,
the lower the demand,</i>

124
00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:33.598
<i>because it's less affordable.</i>

125
00:05:33.633 --> 00:05:35.568 line:10%
<i>But when a price is lowered,
like a sale,</i>

126
00:05:35.603 --> 00:05:36.901
<i>demand goes up.</i>

127
00:05:36.936 --> 00:05:38.570 line:10%
<i>This is called
the demand curve.</i>

128
00:05:38.605 --> 00:05:40.873 line:10%
<i>Now, when you place
the shop owner's supply curve</i>

129
00:05:40.908 --> 00:05:42.408 line:10%
<i>on the customer's
demand curve,</i>

130
00:05:42.443 --> 00:05:44.676 line:10%
<i>You see they move
in opposite directions.</i>

131
00:05:44.711 --> 00:05:46.311
<i>Customers want to spend less,</i>

132
00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:47.980 line:10%
<i>shop owners want you
to spend more.</i>

133
00:05:48.015 --> 00:05:49.248
<i>But there is a point</i>

134
00:05:49.283 --> 00:05:51.416 line:10%
<i>where shop owner
and customers' interests meet.</i>

135
00:05:51.451 --> 00:05:53.451 line:10%
<i>This is where
the two curves intersect.</i>

136
00:05:53.486 --> 00:05:55.455 line:10%
<i>It's where the supply
perfectly matches</i>

137
00:05:55.490 --> 00:05:56.621
<i>the amount of demand.</i>

138
00:05:56.656 --> 00:05:57.623
[record scratches]

139
00:05:57.658 --> 00:05:59.525
[boing, boing]

140
00:06:00.461 --> 00:06:03.195
<i>This is called equilibrium,</i>

141
00:06:03.230 --> 00:06:05.296
<i>and it's beautiful.</i>

142
00:06:05.331 --> 00:06:07.300
♪

143
00:06:10.905 --> 00:06:13.638
<i>Ugh, you haven't heard
a word I've been saying,</i>

144
00:06:13.673 --> 00:06:14.873
<i>have you?</i>

145
00:06:14.908 --> 00:06:17.176
♪

146
00:06:30.791 --> 00:06:32.191
<i>No, no,
wait, wait, wait.</i>

147
00:06:32.226 --> 00:06:33.826
<i>That wasn't supposed
to close yet!</i>

148
00:06:33.861 --> 00:06:36.028
<i>Jonathan? Kristin?
Excuse me!</i>

149
00:06:36.063 --> 00:06:39.865
<i>Where did you--
Oh... my goodness.</i>

150
00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:41.333
[chuckles]

151
00:06:41.368 --> 00:06:42.601
<i>What have I done?</i>

152
00:06:43.636 --> 00:06:45.203
<i>Well, at least
we learned something</i>

153
00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:48.140
<i>about market forces,
and supply and demand, and--</i>

154
00:06:48.175 --> 00:06:49.741
<i>The hell am I talking about?</i>

155
00:06:49.776 --> 00:06:51.210
<i>Just cut it.
Cut.</i>

156
00:06:51.245 --> 00:06:52.211
<i>We're done here.</i>

157
00:06:52.246 --> 00:06:53.511
<i>Somebody get me a drink.</i>

158
00:06:53.546 --> 00:06:54.913
♪

159
00:06:57.851 --> 00:07:00.385
♪

